{"/service/ndnp/nmu/batch_nmu_juniper_ver02/data/sn93061430/0028077425A/1908010301/0011.xml":{"full_text":"I\nI\n5 TIIE MORRISON BROS. STORE\nTHE MORRISON BROS. STORE\nOur Semi -Annual\nSpecial Notice.\nThe readers of the Current\nwho receive the paper this week\nand have not subscribed will\nknow it haa been paid for and no\nbill collector will ever trouble'\nthem for this is one newspaper\nthat ia naver forced on any per\nson and stops when the time ex\npi res.\nWill be the most famous Merchannlse\nEvent ever known in Carlsbad.\nFOR ONE WEEK\nBeginning Monday the 6th.\nand Ending Saturday the 11th.\nHE inauguration of our Semi-Annu-\nal Ked 1 ag Sale will be celebrated\nwilh a week of matchless offerings.\nIt will excel every past effort we have\never made, for these reasons: We\nbought too much goods, have had a mild sea\nson, and the financial panic. All this is the\ncause of accumulation of stock, and we are\ndetermined to reduce our stock and to make\nthis the largest week's business in our history\nof years. Our superior and up-to-date stocks\nare known to you. You positively cannot\nafford to miss such an important occasion as\nthis; we have planned and priced for our\nbiggest week.\nCome to this shopping place Monday,\nTuesday and every day.\nCome and you will not be disappointed\nHffi\nOfS\nu\nCARLSBAD, NEW MEXICO\n6\nThe Methodist ladies will hold\na market at Joyce Pruit-Co's\nstore tomorrow, Saturday, after\nnoon.\nStockmen desiring a reliable\nsaddle made by a reliable firm\nshould leave orders wilh the\nFinlay-Pratt Hardware Co.\nThe missionary priest Rev.\nVincent Frost will be here next\nweek and will commence a mis\nsion in St Ed wards the 12th.\nSam D. Smith and wife re\nturned Wednesday night from a\nvisit to their daughter. Mrs.\nCampbell in Tuttle. I. T. They\ntarried for a few days in Fort\nWorth.\nThe Pecos Valley News of\nArtesia, issued a verry neat\nHoliday number, that in the\nmechanical make-up was a credit\nto the craft and a fine adver\ntisement for Artesia.\nThe Finlay-Pratt Hardware\nCompany have secured the\nservice of a first class harness\nand saddle maker, and will man\nufacture all classes of saddles\nand harness.\nGeo. Cazier, the lessee of the\nHotel Schlitz, sold out this week\nto J. C. Maxwell, formerly of\nHo8well and Mcintosh, N. M.\nHe is a practical hotel man and\nhas already commenced to show\nhis ability to conduct a first class\nhotel the Schlitz being the best\nbetween Arrrarillo and Pecos.\nThe members of the T X cattle\npool were in from their range\nvwirorrlnv nrwl mot in eitv hall to.\nto settle up for the year and pro\nject plans for another year.\nAmong those present were V. P.\nhusk, John Lusk, Geo. Williams,\nG. M. Pendleton, L. L. Fuoss,\nthe Itenson brothers and ethers\ninterested in the pool.\nAt the annual, election last\nnight the Carlsbad Commercial\nt'lub elected J. H. Joyce, Pres.\nand H. A. Houser, Treasurer and\nthe following board of govenors.\nA. N. Pratt. G. M. Cooke. It. H.\nArmstrong. Jno. T. Itolton. W.\nby laws were amended to give\nthe board power to elect a\nsecretary.\nNotice of Special Meeting\nPecos Water Users' Aii'n.\nShareholders will take notice\nthat a special meeting of the As\nsociation will be held in the office\nof the Association \"in Carlsbad,\nN. M., Monday, January 6, 1908\nat 1 p. m. sharp, for the purpose\nof securing a modification of the\norder of the Secretary of the In\nterior, of Dec. 17, 1907, requir\ning the payment of the firHt in\nstallment on Mar. 1, 1908.\nUy order of the Hoard of- Di\nrectors. A. M. Hove, Secretary.\nDec. 31, 1907.\ni 1\nSeven Years of Proof.\n\"I hnv had seven years of proof\nthat Dr. King! 'New Discovery It the\nbest medicine to take (or coughs and\ncolds and for every diM-ased condition\nof throat, chest or lungs,\" says W. V.\nHenry, of Panama, Mo. T b world\nhas had thirty-eight years of proof\nthat Dr. Ding's New Discovery is the\nbest remedy for coughs and colds, la\ngrippe, asthma, hay fever, bronchitis,\nhemorrhage of the lungs, and the ear.\nly stages of consumption. Its timely\nuse always preventa the development\nof pneumonia. Sold nnder guarantee\nat Eddy Drug Co. 60c and VI. Trial\nbottle free.\nHow is Your Digestion?\nMrs. Mary Dowling of No. 22H. 8th\nAve., Sun Francisco, recommends\nremedy for stomach trouble. She rays\n\"Gratitudo fur the wonderful effect of\nElectric Uitteis in a case of acute indi\ngeetion, prompts this testimonial. 1\nam fullv convinced that for stomach\nand livor troubles Electric Bitters is\nthe best remedy on the market today.'\nTl is great tonic and alterative medl\ncine Invigorates the system, purifloe\nthe blond and is especially helpful in\nall forms of female weakness. 60c. at\nEddy Drug Co,\nThe town of Carlsbad is more\nthan fortunate in being located on\nthe banks of the Pecos where\ndrainage t7 a sewer system can be\neffective vith very moderate ex\npens. idd to this the fact that\nthe town has no bonded debt, bet\nter water and more of it than any\nother town in the Pecos Valley\nbesides being the clesnest, best\nshaded, best streets and sidewalks\nand only really reliable irrigation\nsystem covering over thirty thou\nsand acres it is absolutely certain\nto develop into the best town in\nsoutheast New Mexico despite all\nknockers.\nTHK HOY'S CHANCES.\nShrewd business men object to their\nsons learning typewriting and short\nhand.\nThe demand for the publlo school\nboy on the part of business Arms Is i\ngreater than the supply.\nThat la why the Inclusion of type\nwriting and shorthand in a publlo cur\nriculum is a mistake.\nThe prospect of the publlo school\nboy with no Influence to help him la\nnoi rosy iar ouhum iw\ncerned.\nMaliinii for nuhlle school\nboys as clerks, but opportunities do\nnot come to those engaged in clerical\nwork.\nThose who go early to technical\nwork without completing their gen\neral education are constantly unsuo\ncennful Inter on In competing with the\npublic school boy.\nPar-seeing firms are beginning to or-\ngnnlKO their business on civil service\nlines, with progressive salaries and\npensions, so that they can compete\nwith the government service for the\npublic school boy.\nREFLECTIONS Of A BACHELOR.\nA woman Is so deceptive she can\nhave a temper without even red\nbalr.\nNo matter how much a summer va\ncation costs It's worth the money to\nget borne.\nWhen a man Is sane he doesn't\nknow the first thing about wriUng a\nlove letter.\nVSv, 60 YEARS'\nVV yv KXPKRIKNCB\n1 lF\n4 ma.\na I HAM mMfmv\n\"fltl COfVRMlNTe i\nA a.\nA hvam MfiAlrtsT ft ahal h a4 deearlPtMm\natiitair ewoaKtatn mr oimishhi frew tier sua\nliitMilVva la pabtiif pataittartl. VHuiiiMf.\nIhmaaMrrrtlf widantfai. HAttOftOM on faiantft\ntaut fre. (h.1m4 aureit foj aMMn paiar.ta.\nI'atettia taUem ttmniiti Muua ilu, rtirf\natria motlM, vttkHNil a U\nScientific liartea\nA huitfnmrtf IHMtmtP! waottf. AffiH air.\novmthm 01 any fiaiwiia r:Hrnh w-\nif) far lantnib, fa.\nNeuskv\nSuUkr\nSi. Waaklaaiua,\nMIMtWHWi\nAs.\"\nmv\nWatched Fifteen Years.\n\"Kor fifteen years I have watched\nthe working of llucklen's Arnica Salvo\nand It haa never failed to euro any adle\nboll, nicer' or burn to which it was ap-\nptifd. It has saved us many a doctor\nbill,\" says A. F. Hardy, of Eaot Wll\ntoo. Main. 26c. at Eddy Drug Co.\nVaiest lk i wf MM Make I pattern 1 lue fc as)\nBjaavjsjae e4 (keer Myla axxwretcy 4 eseaLtUctly,\nM(CH' (asrtoiThie4 rsehUw)\nBMU ftatk rtW tKa a ot1 1Ah\" MRf-elne. On)\niw'l tMBMt'ltMs(ia Mnamtl turn-, t)av f\nsWeabr, 5 ejaMila). wsHiiltM aia M sCaU s-aa\ntt4 tmmvrm Ca.n jsj fmnm\nmbm .AMraav IMA MvCAU, CO","height":"21788","width":"14228"}}
